<br>
Anything by Dave Barry; &quot;Comeplete Guide to Guys&quot; (considering how Dave is a professional humorist, I find it very funny how informative this book is!)<br>
<br>
Piers Anthony's Xanth books  - *nods* love these....  first read them in 7th grade<br>
<br>
Anything by R.A. Salvatore - inparticular the Drizzt books (of course) and the &quot;Woods Out Back&quot; series (what I first read of his)<br>
<br>
&quot;Voyage of the Bassett&quot; - by someone.  A picture chapter book, and SO beautiful...  buying it at the shelf price of $30 is a steal because you get so much beautiful art.<br>
<br>
&quot;The Princess Bride&quot; by William Goldman - let's just that, in comparison, the movie sucked.  The book is that good.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good Omens&quot; by Terry Pratchett and Neil Gaiman - really funny book!  The back cover: &quot;We hear the world will end on a Saturday.  Next Saturday, in fact.  Just before dinner.  Unfortunately, Sister Mary Loquacious of the Chattering Order has misplaced the Antichrist.  The Four Horsemen of the Apocolypse ride motorcycles.    And the representatives of Heaven and Hell have decided they actually _like_ the human race...  GOOD OMENS  Have a nice doomsday!&quot;  (In the middle of reading it now)<br>
<br>
Anything by Amelia Atwater-Rhodes - she wrote the &quot;In the Forests of the Night&quot; vampire series...  I base all my vampire-lore off of her work.  I love reading these.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hmmm...  all my favorites that I can think of right now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubobmato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobmato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/3/02 12:40:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Great books</span><hr size=1> I too am a big fan of the Dragonlance series.<br>
