<br>
Anne Bishop: Her Black Jewels trilogy is one of the best set of books I have ever read, the woman is damn good at what she does.  And Damon Sadi is just...ROWR.  As is Saetan SaDiablo.  Mmmmm....<br>
<br>
Thomas K. Martin: Magelord Trilogy. 'Nuff said.<br>
<br>
Christopher Golden: The Shadow Saga...great great vampire trilogy. Yum yum.<br>
<br>
Micheal Moorcock has been mentioned, as has Terry Goodkind, Terry Brooks, R.A. Salvatore, Robert Heinlein, Mercedes Lackey, Anne McCaffrey, Peirs Anthony.<br>
<br>
The Light Bearer by Donna Gillespie. Wizard Grove by Tanya Huff. Any Sword and Sorceress books, edited by Marion Zimmer Bradley.<br>
<br>
Mists of Avalon, by Marion Zimmer Bradley.<br>
<br>
Harry Potter!<br>
<br>
Any Bordertown book, most notable being Elsewhere by Will Shetterly.<br>
<br>
The Dark Tower series by Stephen King.<br>
<br>
Tamsin by Peter S. Beagle. The Last Unicorn, also by him.<br>
<br>
DragonLance, anything with the twins in it. I'm in love with Raistlin.<br>
<br>
J. Gregory Keyes: Age of Unreason series.<br>
<br>
Something Wicked This Way Comes by Ray Bradbury.<br>
<br>
Letters from the Earth by Mark Twain.<br>
<br>
White as Snow by Tanith Lee<br>
<br>
The Rats of NIMH but Tim O'Brien<br>
<br>
The Phantom of the Opera by Gaston Leroux<br>
<br>
